A Groovy implementation of GeoScript (http://geoscript.org/).

GeoScript provides geospatial data access, manipulation, and rendering ability to dynamic scripting languages.

Other are implementations written in JavaScript, Python, and Scala.

To build:

Use git to clone the repository:

git clone git://github.com/jericks/geoscript-groovy.git

Use maven to build and test:

mvn clean package

Finally, use maven to create a distribution:

mvn assembly:assembly

The distribution can be found in target/geoscript-groovy-0.97-SNAPSHOT-bin/geoscript-groovy-0.97-SNAPSHOT

GeoScript Groovy has three commands:
1. geoscript-groovy (which can run Groovy files)
2. geoscript-groovysh (which starts a REPL shell)
3. geoscript-groovyConsole (which starts a graphical editor/mini IDE)

See the /examples directory for short examples.
